'''Harald Borgen Bjerke''' (4 March 1860 – 1 April 1926) was a Norwegian businessperson.

He was born in [[Oslo|Kristiania]]. From 1895 to 1912 he was the managing director of Mandalsgatens Høvleri. From 1910 to 1912 he also chaired the [[Norwegian Employers' Confederation]]. From 1918 to 1926 he was the Director-General of [[Norsk Hydro]].<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Harald Borgen Bjerke|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Harald_Borgen_Bjerke|language=Norwegian|accessdate=21 January 2012}}</ref><ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Harald Bjerke|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Ketil Gjølme|last=Andersen|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Harald_Bjerke/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=21 January 2012}}</ref>

He was also a supervisory council member of [[Elektrisk Bureau]].<ref>{{cite news|title=A.s Elektrisk Bureau|date=3 April 1925|work=[[Aftenposten Aften]]|page=5}}</ref>

