'''South Carolina "Carrie" Bronson Hatfield''' (September 9, 1876 &ndash; May 8, 1962) was the wife of former [[Governor of West Virginia]] [[Henry D. Hatfield]] and served as that state's [[First Lady]], 1913-1917.  She was born September 9, 1876, at [[Warfield, Kentucky]]. In 1895, she married [[Henry D. Hatfield]].  As first lady, she hosted social gatherings and participated in [[Charleston, West Virginia|Charleston]] civic affairs. After leaving office, the Hatfields resided in [[Washington, D.C.]] where Gov. Hatfield served a term in the [[United States Senate]], then moved to [[Huntington, West Virginia]] where she died on May 8, 1962.<ref name=wvfl>"West Virginia's First Ladies," West Virginia Division of Culture and History, June 2007.</ref>

